on medium that is on the cells.<\/div><\/div>"}}],"cases":[],"data":null,"html":null,"section":null,"section_color":"#FFED92","section_duration":0,"critical":null,"critical_id":null,"duration":0}],"document":"","materials":[],"description":"<div class = \"text-blocks\"><div class = \"text-block\"><span>Generation of a stable cell line refers to<\/span><span style = \"font-weight:bold;\">the process of developing homogenous populations of cells that demonstrate expression of a transfected gene insert<\/span><span>. The transfected gene integrates into the genome of the host cell, and as a result, are able to express the transfected genetic material.<\/span><\/div><\/div>","changed_on":1628172982}